“DESERT CANVAS” 
-
DROPPING TODAY
7/18
5PM EST 2PM PST
-
This Reaper uses a heavy, distressed canvas for the upper. It is a light tan/natural color. I’m not the first guy to do this, but these are also pretty simple to dye yourself, like I did in the next slide using the colors from the “LAY DOWN YOUR PISTOL” shirt. Use whatever you have…I used leather dye and paint mixed with water
-
THIS IS PRE-ORDER, 8-12 WEEKS

“IF YOU WERE SEVERELY DEHYDRATED OUTSIDE OF LAS VEGAS, NEVADA”
-
DROPPING TODAY
7/18
5PM EST 2PM PST
-
This collection will consist only of tie dye, stone washed and garment dyed pieces. If you were on the brink of death in the Mojave desert after a family vacation in Vegas and you’d step over your own grandmother’s dead body for a single droplet of water, these pieces are what you’d see

node.text:
Hand-painted Hermès Birkin 35 with fully chain-stitched bandana, hand-done by the master himself @tuljutargate 
-
“A HOT DAY IN THE DESERT”
-
This is the first time I’ve used a brush in forever..with a mix of pen and some pastel overlay. Couldn’t be happier with the final product. My man Tul, absolutely murdered the bandana. Thank you again brother.

node.text:
WL “DEATH LIFE EYES” 
-
 This collection will be stone-washed, to emulate the feeling of a vintage piece, which will naturally fade/distress the screen-printed graphic as well. It will also be pre-order for most items. 
 I’m going to give an over-estimate on the lead time because this is a project I’ve been working on for a while and I feel strongly about these pieces. Please read before you buy and understand there will be a wait until you receive the items. Thank you for your patience and support
